                <note rend="inline" type="source">881.512/67: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Diplomatic Agent and Consul General at Tangier</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Blake</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-01-28T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 28, 1929—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5. To supplement the Department’s telegram 4, January 22, 6 p.m. The Department
                    of State will refuse consent to the “padlock law”, and instructions are being
                    sent by pouch for the reply to the French Resident General.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
